  "texts": [
    "The last may respond to a concern about strict regulation and ethical washing (de Laat 2021; Floridi 2019) or, on the other hand, to generate value for their companies by obtaining commercial benefits (Mills et al. 2021).",
    "Although the public sector is the primary beneficiary of these resources, it has a low production of ethical tools, and most of them have a below-average level of development.",
    "Despite this low production of tools, it is notable that governments in the last six years have increased their initiatives and results in AI regulation (Maslej et al. 2023).",
    "Governments must ensure social good by focusing on equity, accountability, sustainability, privacy, and security.",
    "Therefore, they see the need to use and produce tools, including responsibly developed AI-based systems, to improve the quality and reliability of bureaucratic processes."
  ]
}